d opens up new ways of looking at the elevator--as a secular confessional when stalled between floors or as a recurring space in which couples fall in love. Rising upwards through modernity, Lifted takes the reader on a compelling ride through the history of the elevator.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aElevators - Social aspects - History. 0aElevatorsxHistory. 0aElevatorsxSocial aspectsxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479880423.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479880423423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479880423/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles